<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-01-15T23:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-01-15T23:30:00-05:00" n="31" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">690B.9321/1–1653: Telegram</note>
                        <head>No. 31<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Burma (<persName type="from">Sebald</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rangoon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-01-16T11:00:00+06:30">January 16, 1953—11
                                a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1283. … <gloss target="#t_KMT1">KMT</gloss> problem is beginning have
                            repercussions broader in scope than mere military dilemma. Foreign
                                Minister<note n="1" xml:id="d31fn1">Sao Hkun Hkio.</note> also told
                            me <gloss target="#t_KMT1">KMT</gloss> problem is getting completely out
                            of hand, intimated <gloss target="#t_GUB1">GUB</gloss> seriously
                            concerned. Hope Department will speedily urge course of action all
                            interested parties in endeavor assist <gloss target="#t_GUB1">GUB</gloss> find practical solution.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sebald</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>